{"questionId":"30176068","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate power series, as an extension to the Binomial Theorem for negative and fractional indices.</p>\n<p>A power series in <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> is defined as a function of the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {a_0} + {a_1}x + {a_2}{x^2} + {a_3}{x^3} + ...\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span> where the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{a_i} \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>It can be considered as an infinite polynomial.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This is an example of a power series, but is only a finite power series, since only a finite number of the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{a_i}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> are non-zero.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Differentiate the equation obtained part (b) and hence, find the first four terms in a power series for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{ - 2}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{ - 1}} = 1 - x + {x^2} - {x^3} + {x^4} - ...\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 1{\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{ - 2}} =&nbsp; - 1 + 2x - 3{x^2} + 4{x^3} - ...\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{ - 2}} = 1 - 2x + 3{x^2} - 4{x^3} + ...\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30176068","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.1c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Differentiate the equation obtained part (b) and hence, find the first four terms in a power series for ( 1 + x ) − 2 .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.10—Perms and combs, binomial with negative and fractional indices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}